post_text: Shout out to our Junior Varsity! They are 3-1 so far this year. 2 of the 3 wins are against teams that beat us handily last year. They should be proud of the way they are playing good basketball and keep getting better.
text: Shout out to our Junior Varsity! They are 3-1 so far this year. 2 of the 3 wins are against teams that beat us handily last year. They should be proud of the way they are playing good basketball and keep getting better.

post_text: 2 Days = 2 Exciting wins! Every player on the team should be proud of themselves. We played good defense (great defense down the stretch) tonight and we have this season as a whole. These guys, who are typically smaller than the opponent, continue to out-rebound the other teams. We have won the rebound battle EVERY game! And our offense is getting better each and every game. Now, we just need to remain focused on getting better. We have a lot of really good teams on our schedule and some lofty goals that we would like to reach.

post_text:
First week without any games. It is disappointing that the season is over. We will sure miss the seniors that gave their all for the team this season. They set the standard for the current and future players of the program to follow.

It was amazing watching the growth of the team from practice to practice and game to game. Many players improved so much throughout the season that they were nearly unrecognizable by season's end.

I am looking forward to the summer and the future of the program. It will be nice to focus less on installation of offense and defense and focus more on simply getting better.

post_text: Very excited about the future of Indian Basketball. I saw a lot of good things from our youth teams today - boys and girls. Incredible finish to the day... a double overtime win for the boys 51-50. They were down by double digits in the second half but fought back and kept doing what it took to keep themselves alive and get the win. Very impressive!

shared_text:
Terry Pettit
February 21, 2014 at 3:57 PM · USA TODAY ·

An interesting scenario happened at the end of the first half in the Nebraska - Penn State basketball game on Wednesday night. Terran Petteway, Nebraska's leading scorer and a projected 1st round NBA draft pick, was on the bench because he picked up two fouls. Depite his absence the Huskers increased the lead before the end of the half. When the horn blew, instead of hustling off to the locker room Petteway stayed and shook the hand of every player coming off the court. His excitment for his teammates success was genuine. Petteway, beyond being the Huskers best player is also the hardest working practice player. Leadership is many things, including but not limited to, performance, work ethic, and enthuasism for other team members success. I hope Nebraska fans appreciate what they have in Petteway . . . talent is not always accompanied by other leadership traits. He is a special person.

post_text: I am so happy for the seniors. In their last home game they all played well and led the team to a nice win against Conestoga. However, they aren't satisfied and we aren't satisfied as a team. We are looking forward to the challenge of continuing to win games and continuing to move forward.

post_text: Big weekend for Weeping Water activities... wrestlers competing at state, cheerleaders competing at state, the girls basketball team is competing to be one step closer to state, and the boys basketball team is competing against fellow Cass County opponent - Conestoga. Good luck to everyone representing the school and the community! Win or lose, give everything that you've got and make us proud!

post_text: So proud of Collin. Four days after scoring 28 points and grabbing a school record 19 rebounds, he gets interviewed by Huskerland Preps and gets featured on their website. I am glad that he is getting the recognition that he deserves. Hard work pays off.

post_text: Thank you to everyone that made the "Shooting for a Cure" night a success! Thank you to the sponsors that donated a total of $425 that will be given to a member of the community that has been diagnosed with cancer. I would also like to thank everyone that wore their shirts to last night's game. Hopefully we can raise awareness and by doing that, I hope that we can make a difference.

Proud of the guys and proud of how we were able to finish the game. It was one of our most consistent, 4 quarter efforts of the season. Malcolm tried to make a run, but we were able to withstand it and come out on top.

We must now work hard and improve every day so we can finish the season the right way.
